 {"id": "bd-ev-1", "title": "PORT: expand_vars sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::stdlib::wordexp module", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-ev-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T06:49:03.991116Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T06:49:03.991116Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T06:49:03.991116Z", "resolution": "Added crates/frankenlibc-core/src/stdlib/wordexp.rs with: pub enum ExpandError { UndefinedVariable(String) }; pub fn expand_vars<F: Fn(&str) -> Option<String>>(word, undef_is_error, lookup_env) -> Result<String, ExpandError>. Funnels through a private dyn-trait variant (expand_vars_dyn) so the recursive double-quote expansion does not blow up generic monomorphization. Handles backslash escapes, single-quoted (verbatim), $VAR + ${VAR}, double-quoted (recursive), empty $name fallback, unset variable behavior. 20 unit tests cover all of those plus consecutive vars, mixed quoted/unquoted, unclosed brace/quote handling, and verifying the lookup closure receives the exact var name."}
